{
  "texts": [
    "Since then, two main AI movements emerged: the scientific one and the futuristic one [53].",
    "The scientific AI movement supports the idea that formal reasoning is the basis of AI and is investigating whether intelligence can become artificial.",
    "The futuristic AI movement believes that intelligence will become artificial and will influence public opinion to accept that.",
    "While this dichotomy is still vivid, the state-of-the-art of AI is not yet able to prove how intelligence is programmable.",
    "Researchers support that AI today assists humans with ingenuity, contributing to intelligence, not intuition [53]."
  ]
}